<li id="cite_note-zaehnerlastav-106"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-zaehnerlastav_106-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">"The latest of the four Vedas, the Atharva-Veda, is, as we have seen, largely composed of magical texts and charms, but here and there we find cosmological hymns which anticipate the Upanishads, – hymns to Skambha, the 'Support', who is seen as the first principle which is both the material and efficient cause of the universe, to Prāna, the 'Breath of Life', to Vāc, the 'Word', and so on." <a href="#CITEREFZaehner1966">Zaehner 1966</a>, p.&#160;vii.</span>
